        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18788",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Updating to include the Zend_Validate component, as this isn't specific to Zend_Form.\n\nA number of validators include the original value passed to them when creating error messages. We should likely have a way to suppress such functionality on demand; if we did, the Password form element could set this on validators prior to running isValid().",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-01T15:08:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-01T15:08:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18789",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "One possibility is to modify Zend_Form_Element_Password::getMessages() to strip out the value:\n\n{code}\n\/\/ use raw value, as that is what is sent to validator\n$value    = $this->getRawValue();\n$messages = array();\nforeach ($this->_messages as $key => $message) {\n    $messages[$key] => str_replace($value, '', $message);\n}\nreturn $messages;\n{code}\n\nWhile not an ideal solution, it would likely only be used once per request. It is prone to potential error.\n\nFor now, you can very easily modify the messages by passing a 'messages' option to the validator options, with key value pairs of error codes => messages (this can be done from a config, as well).\n\nAdditionally, you can use a Zend_Translate_Adapter to translate error codes to messages; when you attach a translate adapter to a form, it will then translate the error messages accordingly.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-01T16:02:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-01T16:02:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18790",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kschroeder",
                        "name": "kschroeder",
                        "displayName": "Kevin Schroeder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yeah, I've used my own code to work around that with deployable code, but now that it's being merged with what will probably be a very popular module (Building forms from a config file = brilliant)  I think it would be a good idea to have a way to hide the password.  I can help out with that, of course, but I think it would be prudent to have it added before 1.5 goes GA.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kschroeder",
                        "name": "kschroeder",
                        "displayName": "Kevin Schroeder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-01T16:09:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-01T16:09:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18835",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jscherer26",
                        "name": "jscherer26",
                        "displayName": "James Scherer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would suggest substituting *'s for each character in the $value string as the default. Seeing \n\n'****' is less then 6 characters long \n\nseems more intuitively understandable for the user then \n\n'' is less then 6 characters long\n\nwhich suggests a programming problem in my opinion.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jscherer26",
                        "name": "jscherer26",
                        "displayName": "James Scherer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-04T16:56:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-04T16:56:38.000+0000"
                },
